        "gamla-liften": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Gamla liften",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:billingehus"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Gamla liften is the part of the crag outside the nature reserve, south of the narrows, and is described in the guidebook. It begins at the ski slope and extends north towards the narrows. Quite a few routes have been established, with scope for many more.\n\nThe easiest approaches are either from below—park in the ski slope car park and walk up beneath the small lift. Enter the woods where the \"Snowparken\" begins and continue straight up towards the crag.\n\nFrom above, park by the bandy pitch. Walk behind the hotel and descend between the ski slope and the chapel. Take care not to walk in front of the chapel’s panoramic windows!!\n\nTwo fixed ropes have been installed for ascent and descent and are easiest to locate from below. One is between routes 5 and 9, and the other between routes 35 and 41.\n\nThe first section begins immediately beside the ski slope.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:billingehus"
            ]
          }
        },
